In this article, President Joseph R. Biden Jr. discusses the importance of Armed Forces Day and honors the members of the Army, Navy, Air Force, Marine Corps, Space Force, Coast Guard, and National Guard and Reserve forces. He highlights that these service members not only make up the world's finest fighting force but also embody the best qualities of the nation. The article emphasizes the dedication and sacrifices made by service members and their families, caregivers, and survivors. President Biden mentions significant milestones such as the 50th anniversary of the all-volunteer force, the desegregation of the military, and women's integration, highlighting the strength and capabilities that diversity brings to the Armed Forces. He also discusses the administration's efforts to support veterans, including signing bipartisan bills and expanding access to mental health care. President Biden underscores the importance of creating a safe and inclusive environment within the military, including the removal of the ban on openly transgender people serving and reforms in investigating and prosecuting sexual assault and harassment. The article concludes with a call to honor the courage, sacrifice, and service of the Armed Forces on Armed Forces Day and encourages Americans to display the flag and participate in local observances of the day.